Methodology 3


Data Preparation

The data cleaning process involved handling missing values, standardizing formats, removing duplicates, correcting inconsistencies. This preparation ensured that the data was structured, enriched, and optimized for predictive modeling and visualization.





Model Selection

A classification-based approach was used to predict churn, effectively handling complex interactions among multiple variables. Key factors like customer segment, engagement levels, and sales history have non-linear relationships with churn rates. This model captures these patterns without requiring extensive data preprocessing. The ensemble method, combining multiple decision trees, improves accuracy and reduces overfitting, making it a strong solution for predicting churn. This approach enables more precise retention strategies, helping businesses optimize customer engagement and reduce churn effectively.




Model Development

The XGBClassifier model was trained and optimized using electronic sales data. The dataset was split into training and testing sets. The training set enabled the model to identify patterns, while the testing set assessed its ability to generalize to unseen data. This approach helps prevent overfitting, ensuring the model doesnt perform well only on the training data but also on new, unseen data. By using a test set, the models predictions remain unbiased and reliable.
